The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 3: Indias forex reserves increased by $924 million to $179.052 billion during the week ended January 26 against $178.128 billion in the week ended January 19. Reserves were up by $702 million during the preceding week. The foreign currency assets also increased by $916 million to $171.984 billion during the week, according to figures released by the Reserve Bank of India. Foreign currency assets in dollars include the effect of revaluation of non-US currencies such as euro, sterling and yen.

 Lucknow, Feb. 3: Steel Authority of India Ltd (SAIL) may start manufacturing activities in Uttar Pradesh by setting up a plant in the state, minister of state for steel and mines Akhilesh Das said here today.

 New Delhi, Feb. 3: Ballarpur Industries (BILT) chairman Gautam Thapar has inherited the shares and voting rights held by its late chairman emeritus Lalit Mohan Thapar. A meeting of the share transfer committee of the company had approved the move, a company official said.




